-- 
Nigeria Releases New Regulations for Minerals, Guardian Reports

-- B y   E l i s h a   B a l a - G b o g b o
-- 
2011-05-25T08:44:36Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-25/nigeria-releases-new-regulations-for-minerals-guardian-reports.html
Nigeria presented new minerals and
mining regulations for foreign investors to companies yesterday,
the Guardian reported, citing Mines Minister Musa Sada.  The guidelines bring rules for the industry in line with
international best practices, the Lagos-based  newspaper  cited
the minister as saying.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Elisha Bala-Gbogbo in Abuja at 
 ebalagbogbo@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net  